I am trying to convert the following recursive function to a non-recursive equation: $$
f(n) =
\begin{cases}
0,&\text{if n = 0;}\newline
2 \times f(n -1) + 1,&\text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
$$ I have calculated the results for $n = 1$ through to $n = 6$ but I cannot find a discernible pattern from which to make an equation. The results are: $$f(1) = 1$$ $$f(2) = 3$$ $$f(3) = 7$$ $$f(4) = 15$$ $$f(5) = 31$$ $$f(6) = 63$$ I hope I have formatted this correctly (my first time using LaTex), and if anyone could offer any help that would be greatly appreciated.

